Clarence Thomas completed five days of grueling days of testimony, apparently well on 
his way to becoming the second black justice in the history of the Supreme Court.  
Thomas, a federal judge, was picked by President Bush to replace Thurgood Marshall, 
the high court's only black justice.</SUM>
